room_title: Escape room "Jackie's Last Call" by MetaCog Escape Games in Hutchinson
room_description:
Jackie Adam was one of the greatest female Poker players of the 1980s, especially in the realm of 3-Card Poker. With her great bluffing skills and amazing luck, she had numerous Poker tournaments under her belt. History would have deemed her as "Black-Hand" Jackie.
Before she passed away, she left a note to any Poker player or fanatic stating that all of her winnings over the years are open to any that might successfully find it. The note alludes that it may be found in one of the private rooms at Wintuck Casino.
It's now open to the public for any who dare to try to find her winnings, but only have 60 minutes to do so. Can you find Jackie Adam's Loot in time or will you fold under the pressure?
